#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:8
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:11
msgid "What does Scrum mean?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:13
msgid ""
"In Agile software development, a daily meeting in which each developer "
"describes what they have been doing, what they plan to do next, and any "
"impediments to progress."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:17
msgid ""
"Scrum is a management and control process that cuts through complexity to"
" focus on building software that meets business needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:20
msgid ""
"Scrum meeting is conducted daily for 15 minutes, where members are asked "
"main three questions; “What did you do since last meeting?”, “What will "
"you do today?” and “What impediments do you have in your way?”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:25
msgid "Purpose of Scrum in Agile Development"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:27
msgid ""
"To support agile terms in collaborative and coordinating their work with "
"other terms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:30
msgid ""
"Here in Flectra, we have introduced Scrum Management with Project Module,"
" where we have tried to fulfill all the functionalities of Agile Software"
" Development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:35
msgid "Sprint Dashboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:37
msgid ""
"You will get statistical counts of Sprints, Tasks, Stories, Project for "
"all at once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:40
msgid ""
"Dashboard gives you the idea of scrum where you can see a Burndown chart,"
" which shows number of sprints with its Estimated Velocity and Actual "
"Velocity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:48
msgid "Project Team"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:50
msgid ""
"Project Team is a group of experts in different technologies with "
"different skills, who are liable for project development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:56
msgid "Attributes of the project team are as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:58
msgid ""
"Scrum Master : A scrum master is a facilitator for an agile development "
"team. The scrum master manages the process of how information is "
"exchanged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:60
msgid ""
"Members : Members are Project developers who are expert in particular "
"field or technology."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:61
msgid "Project : The task or responsibility, the team is allocated for."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:62
msgid ""
"Team Strength : Team strength describes the expertise level of the team, "
"which describes team member with their skills."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:64
msgid ""
"Description : Description describes the overview of the project, which "
"gives idea to the members of the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:67
msgid "Sprint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:69
msgid ""
"In product development, a sprint is a set of period of time during which "
"specific work has to be completed and made ready for review."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:75
msgid ""
"Task is compartmentalized between few parts which are covered by a single"
" sprint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:77
msgid "Sprint contains attributes which are as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:79
msgid "Project - The associated project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:80
msgid "Team - The team, working on sprint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:81
msgid "Duration - Duration of the sprint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:82
msgid "Daily Scrum Time - The time when scrum meeting is to be conducted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:83
msgid "Velocity - Velocity indicates the complexity of the sprint in points."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:84
msgid ""
"Sprint Planning - This shows the productivity hours spent by each member "
"of the project scrum"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:86
msgid ""
"We have put smart buttons to the top right corner of the sprint, which "
"shows Tasks, Stories, Release Plannings and Retrospectives according to "
"the current sprint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:90
msgid "Velocity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:92
msgid ""
"Velocity is the measure of the amount of work a team can tackle during a "
"single sprint and is the key metric in Scrum. Velocity is calculated in "
"the end of the sprint by totalling the points of all fully completed "
"tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:99
msgid ""
"Velocity in the sprint is calculated by adding velocity of all the tasks "
"related to the sprint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:102
msgid "Sprint Planning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:104
msgid ""
"Here is a calculation of sprint planning, which shows Productivity time "
"given to the sprint by each member of the team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:107
msgid "Productivity Hours Calculation for team member"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:109 ../../scrum/scrum.rst:117
msgid ""
"Available Percentage - Availability of particular team member in "
"percentage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:110
msgid "Business Days - Start date of the sprint - End date of the sprint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:111
msgid "Number of days - Number of working days of the week"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:113
msgid ""
"Productivity Hours = [Available Percentage * Business Days * Number of "
"days] / 100"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:115
msgid "Sprint Hours Calculation for team member"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:118
msgid "Business Days - start date of the sprint - end date of the sprint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:119
msgid "Productivity Hours = Working hours / Total Hours"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:121
msgid ""
"Sprint Hours = [Available Percentage * Business Days * Productivity "
"Hours] / 100"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:123
msgid "Total Hours Calculation for team member"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:125
msgid "[Total Hours = Sprint hours - Holiday count(In Hours) - Off hours]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:128
msgid "Project Story"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:130
msgid ""
"Project Stories are one of the primary development artifact for scrum "
"project team. A user story is a very high-level definition of a "
"requirement, containing just enough information so that the developers "
"can produce a reasonable estimate of the effort to implement it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:138
msgid ""
"A story may contain multiple tasks, there may have a single story "
"containing all the user requirements for Project tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:141
msgid "Attributes of Project Story are as follow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:143
msgid "Sprint : The sprint which is associated to the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:144
msgid "Priority : Priority of the story"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:145
msgid "Owner : Owner of the story (Who wrote the story)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:146
msgid "Estimated Velocity/Actual Velocity : Velocity of the story"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:147
msgid "Description : Description of the story"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:149
msgid ""
"Velocity of the story is calculated by totalling the velocity of each "
"task related to the current story."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:153
msgid "Release Planning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:155
msgid ""
"A very high-level plan for multiple Sprints is created during the Release"
" Planning. It is a guideline that reflects the expectations about which "
"feature will be implemented and when they are completed. It also serves "
"as a base to monitor progress within the project. Release can be "
"intermediate deliveries done during the project or the final delivery at "
"the end."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:164
msgid ""
"One sprint can have multiple release plannings according to the task "
"divided into several subtasks. Whichever subtask is completed first, will"
" be treated for releasing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:168
msgid "Attributes of Release Planning are as follows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:170
msgid "Sprint - Sprint associated to the release planning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:171
msgid ""
"Priority - How important the current release planning is, that is shown "
"by priority."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:172
msgid "Release Date - Date of Releasing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:173
msgid ""
"Tasks - Number of tasks, which shows that how many of them are going to "
"be released under the plan."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:176
msgid "Retrospective"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:178
msgid ""
"Retrospective is meeting that helds at the end of an iteration of "
"development life cycle. During the retrospective, the team reflects on "
"what happened in the and identifies actions for improvement  going "
"forward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:185
msgid ""
"The sprint retrospective is meeting facilitated by the Scrum Master at "
"which the team discusses sprint and determines what could be changed that"
" might make the next sprint more productive. The sprint review looks at "
"what the team is building, whereas the retrospective looks at how they "
"are building it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:190
msgid "Attributes of Retrospective are as follow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:192
msgid "Sprint - The sprint which is going through the retrospective."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:193
msgid "Retrospective Method - Method, that is used for the retrospective process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:194
msgid "Scrum Master - The one who held the process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../scrum/scrum.rst:195
msgid ""
"Retrospective Lines - It has two fields, User and Message, where the "
"current logged in user gives the review on the Sprint as per the process."
msgstr ""

